About Me

The Person
Behind the Marks

I'm a graphic designer based in San Luis Obispo, California, specializing in logo and brand identity design. I believe a great logo isn't just something that looks good — it's a visual strategy that makes people stop, look twice, and remember.

My work spans abstract marks, mascots, wordmarks, monograms, pictorial marks, and combination logos. Each project is custom-built from the ground up, never templated, always intentional.

When I'm not designing, I'm studying brands that changed industries — obsessing over what makes some marks iconic and others forgettable.

Got Questions?

Frequently Asked

How long does a logo project take? +
Most custom logos are delivered within 5–10 business days from the project kickoff. Rush timelines are available for an additional fee — just mention it when you reach out.
What file formats will I receive? +
You'll receive fully editable vector files (AI, EPS, SVG) plus high-resolution raster exports (PNG with transparent background, PDF). Every package includes both color and black & white versions.
Do I own the logo after purchase? +
Yes — 100%. Upon final payment, full commercial rights transfer to you. You can trademark it, sell products with it, and use it across all channels without any royalty fees.
What if I don't like the initial concepts? +
Every package includes revision rounds to ensure you're completely satisfied. The Signature and Premium packages include unlimited revisions. I won't close a project until you love your logo.
How do I pay? +
Payments are processed securely via Stripe. I require a 50% deposit to begin, with the balance due before final file delivery. All major credit and debit cards accepted.
Can you match a specific style I have in mind? +
Absolutely. The more reference material and direction you can share upfront, the better. I'll ask you to complete a brief that captures your vision, target audience, competitors, and aesthetic preferences before I start designing.
